The following definition, for ${\mathbb{E}}_\infty$-ring spectra in the symmetric monoidal simplicial model category of ${\mathbb{S}}$-modules, is due to Rognes \cite{rog}. It was later generalized by Roth to ${\mathbb{E}}_1$-ring spectra, again using the category of ${\mathbb{S}}$-modules \cite{froth}. Our definition below generalizes both of these definitions and only differs in that it is phrased in the language of quasicategories. The motivating example that should be kept in mind is the unit morphism ${\mathbb{S}}\to MU$ from the sphere spectrum to the complex cobordism spectrum, as described in \cite{rog}.


\begin{defi}[Hopf-Galois Extensions]
Let $H$ be a cocommutative ${\mathbb{E}}_n$-bialgebra in ${\mathcal{S}}$ and $A$ an ${\mathbb{E}}_m$-algebra in $CoMod_H$ that is a trivial $H$-comodule. Let $B$ be an ${\mathbb{E}}_m$-algebra in $CoMod_H$, $\phi:A\to B$ a morphism of ${\mathbb{E}}_m$-algebras and assume that $H$ coacts on $B$ over $A$. If:
\begin{enumerate}
\item the composite morphism $B\otimes_AB\overset{1\otimes c}\to B\otimes_AB\otimes H\overset{\mu_B\otimes 1}\to B\otimes H$ is an equivalence of ${\mathbb{E}}_n$-ring spectra, and
\item the cotensor product $B\Box_H {\mathbb{S}}$ exists and the canonical $A$-algebra map $A\to B\Box_H{\mathbb{S}}$ is an equivalence, 
\end{enumerate} 
then we say that the map $\phi:A\to B$ is an \textit{$H$-Hopf-Galois extension of ${\mathbb{E}}_m$-ring spectra}.
\end{defi}


