The composition is given by a 2-simplex in the quasicategory of ${\mathbb{E}}_{n-1}$-monoidal quasicategories, hence by a morphism of simplicial sets in $Hom(\Delta^2,Hom({\mathbb{E}}_{n-1}^\otimes,{q\mathcal{C}at}))\simeq Hom(\Delta^2\times{\mathbb{E}}_{n-1}^\otimes,{q\mathcal{C}at}).$ By the quasicategorical Grothendieck construction of \cite{htt}, we obtain a coCartesian fibration of simplicial sets $p:\mathcal{M}^\otimes\to \Delta^2\times {\mathbb{E}}_{n-1}^\otimes$ such that $p^{-1}(0)\simeq G^\otimes$, $p^{-1}(1)\simeq G/H^\otimes$ and $p^{-1}(2)\simeq \ast^\otimes$, where $G^\otimes$, $G/H^\otimes$ and $\ast^\otimes$ are the $\infty$-operads witnessing the ${\mathbb{E}}_{n-1}$-monoidal structure on $G$, $G/H$ and $\ast$. The projection map induces a family of $\infty$-operads $\mathcal{M}^\otimes\to \Delta^2$. This projection is a flat fibration as it satisfies the requirements of Example B.3.4 of \cite{ha}, i.e. there are coCartesian lifts of every edge in $\Delta^2\simeq\Delta^2\times\ast\subset\Delta^2\times{\mathcal{F}in_\ast}$. 
\end{proof}

